		<div class="post" id="post-4374109">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4374109)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4374109">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/gene-r" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(634139); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=634139&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227421" alt="Gene R" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=634139)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/gene-r" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(634139); return false;" >Gene R</a></span> <span class="odate time_1569317874 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Sep 2019 09:37</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4374109">
									

<p>I kinda disagree with the author here. Morals and attitude towards resources change depending on said resources' availability. If I were to throw away a loaf of stale bread, no one would say a word. If I were to do the same in a starving, war-wracked city, repercussions would be severe.<br />
Same goes here - poking an actress with a knife in our world may result in someone dying and someone doing the time for it. Doing the same in a world where no one can die and bodies are a dime a dozen probably won't amount to much. Therefore, the spectators here would not be &quot;depraved cannibals&quot;, as the author is trying to portray them. More like &quot;seekers of cheap thrill&quot;.</p>

							</div>

								
					
						<div class="options">
				
													<strong><a href="javascript:;" onclick="postReply(event,4374109)" class="btn btn-primary btn-small btn-sm">Reply</a></strong> 
