    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-4374750">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-4374750">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4374750)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4374750">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tufto" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3337265); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3337265&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227421" alt="Tufto" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3337265)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tufto" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3337265); return false;" >Tufto</a></span> <span class="odate time_1569355307 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Sep 2019 20:01</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4374750">
									

<p>Well, the point wasn't to imply that they were depraved cannibals for the simple reason that their tastes in their context don't align with our own. They're not cannibals for using their lack of death as a resource; they're cannibals because that serves as a mask for a greater degree of exploitation.</p>
<p>Nadia may not be able to die, but she is still poor. She has to put herself through a great deal of public pain and humiliation in order to feed herself and look after her grandmother. Getting stabbed still hurts. Bleeding out on stage, suffering the physical pain that causes death even if the death itself does not occur, is still an immensely tragic experience for her. She is willing to put herself through all sorts of trauma just because of the chance to succeed within the unequal power structures of this new world.</p>
<p>It is for this reason that they're depraved cannibals: without the big taboo of death looming over them, they feel more excused in their cruelties. Nobody dies, so who cares how many people get hurt? In this version of EoD, people used the alterations to the social order to intensify and smuggle in ways to extend their own power of interests, and the fallout is the ordinary people on the ground, as ever.</p>

							</div>

								
					
